  "text": "Warrender et. al compared STIDE, RIPPER, and HMM-based methods in [CITATION_1] . They concluded that all methods performed adequately, while HMM gave the best accuracy on average. However, it required higher computational resources and storage space, since it makes multiple passes through the training data, and stores significant amount of intermediate data, which is computationally expensive, especially for large traces.",
